h3. Issue Summary
Labels containing *+* characters are not able to be deleted. 
In our internal logs we can see the character is not being HTML encoded and is therefore taken as literal  for example:


h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a confluence page.
 # Add a label containing a *+* symbol.
 # Try to delete the label.  

h3. Expected Results
 # The label should be deleted.
 # The label should not able to created.

h3. Actual Results
The label is created and subsequently cannot be removed via the UI and the below error is displayed:
 !image-2019-09-24-12-41-50-977.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Notes
This error is not immediately helpful, however trying to remove the label via making a DELETE call to the {{/wiki/rest/api/content/<contentId>/label?name=10+10}} endpoint returns the below:
{code:json}
{
    "statusCode": 404,
    "data": {
        "authorized": false,
        "valid": true,
        "errors": [],
        "successful": false
    },
    "message": "com.atlassian.confluence.api.service.exceptions.NotFoundException: No label found with name: 10"
}
{code}


h3. Workaround
You are able to workaround this by adjusting the URL and replacing the offending *+* with *%2B* and making the DELETE call via REST eg.
{code:bash}
curl -X DELETE \
  -u <user_email>:<api_token> \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Accept-Encoding: gzip, deflate' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  'https://<siteName>.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/<contentId>/label?name=10%2B10'
{code}

It's also possible to use the following code directly on the browser's console:
{code:javascript} fetch(
    "https://{instance}/wiki/rest/api/content/{content_id}/label/{label_name}",
    {
        "credentials":"include",
        "headers":{
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        },
        "method":"DELETE"
    }
).then((resp) => function(response){
    console.log(response);
}); {code}

h3. Issue Summary
When we have an *Expand macro* that contains an *Attachments macro* within the expand box, it gets the width changed after saving the template - it can be saw editing the template after saving or creating a new page using this template.

h3. Environment
* Cloud
* New Editing Experience

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new template or edit an existing one;
# Add an *Expand macro*;
# Inside the expand box, add a *Attachments macro* - note the width, centered as default;
# For comparing reasons, add another *Expand macro* with some random text;
# Save the template;
# Edit this template or create a new page using it;

h3. Expected Results
The *Expand macro* with the *Attachments* one keeps the same width as the other expand.

h3. Actual Results
The width of the first added expand gets slightly bigger than the original size.

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

