h3. Summary
* Create From Template Macro does not fill page title does not add template labels when using a user-created space level template
h3. Environment
* New Editor


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create either a Global or Space level template using the new editor;
# Add a label during the template creation and save it;
# Insert a "Create from template" macro into a test page;
# On "Template name" select the newly created template;
# On "Title of page to be created" give a title to new pages;
# Save and publish this new page;
# Once the page is published click on its *Create from template* button.

h3. Expected Results
* Pages to be created from template, with names and labels
h3. Actual Results
* Pages are created using the template, however the *page's name* is not populated and no labels are added to this newly created page
 


h3. Workaround
* Instead of using *Create from template* user can create pages using the template by:
# Clicking on the *+* button on the left pane > select the desired template 
(this will populate pages' title and labels)
